http://www.thehindu.com/news/cities/Visakhapatnam/Attempts-to-dilute-CRZ-norms-decried/article14009871.ece

Former Union Energy Secretary E.A.S. Sarma on Tuesday vehemently opposed efforts to relax Coastal Regulation Zone (CRZ) norms to promote beach tourism in the State.Reacting to a news item published in these columns on pressure being mounted on the Centre to relax the norms to allow beachside constructions, Mr. Sarma in a letter to the Secretary, Ministry of Environment and Forests underlined the need to further strengthen CRZ regulations to protect the coastal environment. He said local real estate developers and industrialists had been exerting pressure on MoEF to relax the CRZ requirements.